{"id":669473342,"lang":"javascript","lang_name":"JavaScript","time":"1 year, 2 months","timestamp":1648533215,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"133 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/669473342/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Median of Two Sorted Arrays","memory":"48.1 MB","code":"/**\n * @param {number[]} nums1\n * @param {number[]} nums2\n * @return {number}\n */\nvar findMedianSortedArrays = function(nums1, nums2) {\n    //let num = [...nums1, ...nums2]\n    //num.sort((a, b) => {return a-b})\n    \n    let i = 0, j = 0\n    let num = []\n    \n    while (i < nums1.length || j < nums2.length) {\n        \n        if (nums1[i] < nums2[j]) {\n          num.push(nums1[i])\n          i++\n        } else if (nums1[i] > nums2[j]) {\n          num.push(nums2[j])\n          j++;\n        } else if(nums1[i] === nums2[j]) {\n            num.push(nums1[i])\n            num.push(nums2[j])\n            i++\n            j ++\n        } else { //control goes to this block if any array becomes empty\n            if(nums1.length === i){\n                num.push(...nums2.splice(j))\n            } else if(nums2.length === j){\n                num.push(...nums1.splice(i))\n            }\n        }\n    }\n   \n    if (num.length % 2 > 0) return num[(num.length-1)/2]\n    return (num[(num.length/2)] + num[(num.length/2) - 1])/2\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"median-of-two-sorted-arrays","has_notes":false}
